"default (testrun can be modified with --runpytest=subprocess to create "
"subprocesses in many places instead).  The main APIs to run pytest in a test "
"is \"runpytest()\" or \"runpytest_subprocess\" and \"runpytest_inprocess\" "
"if you need a particular way of running the test.  In all cases you get back "
"a RunResult but the inprocess one will also have a \"reprec\" attribute with "
"the recorded events/reports."
